    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You cannot expect to parse a date with a SimpleDateFormat that is set up with a different format.  </p>\n\n<p>To parse your \"Thu Jun 18 20:56:02 EDT 2009\" date string you need a SimpleDateFormat like this (roughly):</p>\n\n<pre><code>SimpleDateFormat parser=new SimpleDateFormat(\"EEE MMM d HH:mm:ss zzz yyyy\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Use this to parse the string into a Date, and then your other SimpleDateFormat to turn that Date into the format you want.</p>\n\n<pre><code>        String input = \"Thu Jun 18 20:56:02 EDT 2009\";\n        SimpleDateFormat parser = new SimpleDateFormat(\"EEE MMM d HH:mm:ss zzz yyyy\");\n        Date date = parser.parse(input);\n        SimpleDateFormat formatter = new SimpleDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd\");\n        String formattedDate = formatter.format(date);\n\n        ...\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>JavaDoc: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
