    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>How about <a href=\"http://www.jdatepicker.com/docs/api/com/standbysoft/component/date/swing/JDateComponent.html#getSelectedDate()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">getSelectedDate</a>? Anyway, specifically on your code question, the problem is with this line:</p>\n\n<pre><code>new SimpleDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The string that goes in the constructor has to match the format of the date. The documentation for how to do that is <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>. Looks like  you need something close to \"EEE MMM d HH:mm:ss zzz yyyy\" </p>\n"
